CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 11, 1953, pg. 16 reads: "Delta Easter Symposium - The twenty-seventh annual Easter Symposium given by Delta Sigma Theta sorors in Pittsburgh, had the above talented group as participants in affair, held at the Centre Avenue YMCA. Left to right: Julie Miller Melman, violinist; Elizabeth Youngue, vocalist; Mary Baltimore, chairman of the day's events; Vivian Richman, guitarist, and Patricia Prattis, pianist. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Delta Sigma Theta sorority members, from left: violinist Julie Miller Melman, vocalist Elizabeth Youngue, Mary Baltimore, guitarist Vivian Richman, and pianist Patricia Prattis (Jennings), standing in Centre Avenue YMCA for annual Easter Symposium
